  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Pro-Cacao: Promoting the economic and social inclusion of producers in the cocoa chain in Venenillo</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cocoa producers</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project seeks to improve living conditions of 90 cocoa producing families in Venenillo (Hu&#xE1;nuco Department) and  increase their market access for certified cocoa certified through compliance with social and environmental criteria of UTZ and Rainforest Alliance. The project is co-funded by LWR and CAMSA. Objectives are: 
a) Promote best practices in environmental conservation and occupational health and safety management in cocoa production for 90 farmers and their families
b) Improve the living conditions of 90 households through the promotion of improved stoves, water and sanitation. 
c) Promote local participation to increase public investment in basic services (water, sewage, road access, electricity) in the town of Venenillo.</narrative>
  </description>
